results.title: If not now, when? [electronic resource] : how to take charge of your career / by Camilla Arnold and Jane Barrett.
abstracts: The world of work is changing dramatically. Jobs for life have long been a thing of the past and even as people move up the corporate ladder, they are questioning their choices and keen to consider new possibilities such as work/life balance and portfolio working. Those of us keen to change career often don't know where to start so it remains a pipe dream rather than a reality we can work towards. In this action-oriented and pragmatic book, expert career coaches Jane Barrett and Camilla Arnold address the common barriers to career change that they frequently encounter in their work, and give r.

More than money [electronic resource] : questions every MBA needs to answer : redefining risk and reward for a life of purpose / Mark Albion.
abstracts: MBA students are chronically risk-averse. Their risk aversion prevents them from seeking and living a life of meaning and purpose. This book redefines the meaning of risk, and/or asks business students to look at risk in a new way. It shows students that the choices they think of as "safe" (e.g. lucrative jobs that fulfill no personal aspirations aside from financial gain, deferring service to others until retirement, etc.) are actually quite risky, since they typically lead us to sell our souls. A consciousness-raising book rather than a how-to, Albion helps MBA students give themse.

results.title: Successful interview skills [electronic resource] : how to prepare, answer tough questions and get your ideal job / Rebecca Corfield.
abstracts: This useful guide shows readers how to portray professionalism and confidence and take control of the interview process. Breaking the process down into accessible steps, Rebecca Corfield identifies the way to prepare for an interview, providing example questions and advice on how to answer them. There are also tips on what employers are looking for, how to make a presentation during an interview, and how to create a good and lasting impression.

24 hours to the perfect interview [electronic resource] : quick steps for planning, organizing & preparing for the interview that gets the job / Matthew J. DeLuca & Nanette F. DeLuca.
abstracts: Being well-prepared gives the job candidate confidence, control, the upper hand, while being unprepared the surest way to be overlooked. Yet even though the key to a successful interview is being prepared, job seekers frequently have only a short time to determine what to bring, what to wear, and what to say to all the questions they are asked. They need a one-stop guide that organizes every detail of the interview for them and gives them the advantage over the competition. In 24 Hours to the Perfect Interview, the authors of the bestselling Best Answers to the 201 Most Frequently Asked Interview Questions offer quick and easy steps that prepare job seekers for the perfect interview. In each chapter, Matt and Nan Deluca break down their winning career advice into easy-to-follow steps readers can use as they prepare themselves for every interview. At the end of every chapter is a checklist where readers can actually check off each stage of the interview they have finished preparing for. All aspects of the interview are covered, including: Researching the company and the position; Brainstorming stories that illustrate your experience; Putting together the perfect professional look.
